article.headline: UNC Greensboro 73, UNC Wilmington 66
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- Ricky Hickman scored 23 points and grabbed six rebounds to lead UNC Greensboro to 73-66 win Saturday night over UNC Wilmington. The Seahawks (6-20) outscored the Spartans (15-12) in the second half and had more players in double figures, but couldn't over UNC Greensboro's 10-point halftime lead. Mikko Koivisto scored 11 points for the Spartans and Kyle Hines added 10 and six rebounds. Jeff Horowitz scored 14 points for the Seahawks and Vladimir Kuljanin scored 13 and grabbed 10 rebounds. Todd Hendley scored 11 points and Montez Downey had 10 along with five rebounds.
